The technical regulator of '''communications in Chile''' is the Ministry of Transportation and Telecommunications, through the Undersecretariat of Telecommunications (Subtel).Telephone*Main lines in use: 3.379 million (2007)*Mobile cellular: 24.130.754 (2012) (devices)**Pre-paid: 17.283.257**Post-paid: 6.847.497*System: privatization began in 1988; advanced telecommunications infrastructure; modern system based on extensive microwave radio relay facilities; fixed-line connections have dropped in recent years as mobile-cellular usage continues to increase, reaching a level of 85 telephones per 100 persons"CIA"**Domestic: extensive microwave radio relay links; domestic satellite system with 3 earth stations**international: country code - 56; submarine cables provide links to the US and to Central and South America; satellite earth stations - 2 Intelsat (Atlantic Ocean) (2007)Radio*Broadcast stations: 1,490 (175 AM; 1,315 FM) (2006)[Compendio Estad√≠stico 2006], INE.TelevisionTelevision in Chile*Broadcast stations: 63 (plus 121 repeaters) (1997)"CIA"*Broadcast television system: NTSC*Pay television: 4.158.874 (2012)[Articulo 2012], Cambio21.InternetInternet in Chile*Internet hosts: 847,215 (2008)"CIA"*Internet users: 5.57 million (2007)"CIA"*Internet mobile users: 4.921.587"Desarrollo Digital"*Internet country code: .cl"CIA"Other technical details*Voltage: 220 volts AC, 50 HzReferencesTelecommunications inChile